<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880831-0041 </DOCNO><HL> Treasury to Sell Bills Totaling $14 Billion, Redeem $13.7 Billion </HL><SO> </SO><IN> FIN BON </IN><G> TRE </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Treasury plans to raise $300 million in new cash with the sale Tuesday of about $14 billion in short-term bills to redeem $13.7 billion in maturing bills.    The offering will be divided evenly between 13-week and 26-week bills maturing Dec. 8, 1988, and March 9, 1989, respectively.    Tenders for the bills, available in minimum $10,000 denominations, must be received by 1 p.m. EDT Tuesday at the Treasury or at Federal Reserve banks or branches. </TEXT></DOC>